===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|p}} — a tool similar to a knife ({{zh-ref|Li Xueqin, 2012}}), perhaps a sickle; see also [[辛]]. In some other versions both on oracle bones and bronzes, it looks like a huge pair of scissors used to cut weed. The original meaning of "mow, cut weed; sickle" is preserved in [[刈]]. Unrelated to [[爻]].

===Etymology===
Sense "regulate, govern, orderly" is derived from "to mow, cut, reap"; this sense's origin is ambiguous, possibly from "to cut" > "to trim", etc. ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). If so, see {{zh-l|刈}} for etymology.

Alternatively, from {{zh-l|禦}} (ibid.)

